The premise of Project GreenCell is to help make aware of the importance of cellphone recycling. Cellphones in this day have become a pervasive object, carried around by almost everyone. Most people probably have a few old cellphones lying around their houses and probably never thought of recycling the old cellphone(s) as it just sits there collecting dust. While this is a bit of an assumption, it can be safely assumed that there are a lot of unused cellphones due to the massive number of people who own a cellphone and as new cellphones come out, old ones are forgotten.  With the country‚Äôs transition towards helping the environment, it can be safely assumed that there are people who are willing to recycle their old cellphones.  Due to the increasing shortage of materials, there is a high demand from manufacturers for old cellphones that can be recycled for various rare earth metals.  This is where our project comes in, dubbed Project GreenCell.

1. Flyers and posters will be created to promote our Project GreenCell and will be placed in strategic locations around Orange and LA County. The advertisement will focus on how recycling cell phones protects the environment.
2.  A certificate of donation for donors who donate their phones to us.
3. Our website will provide a complete description about the project, list all the phones that are currently on sale along with their information, and also information on recycling.
4.  The website will also accommodate people who wants to donate their cell phone by listing the address they can drop off or mail their cell phone.
5. An email form will be available on the website so that potential donors or customers can communicate directly with our staff.
6. Appropriate security to allow personal information to flow from clients to our staff using the website forms.
7. All phones received will be labeled with their information and packaged in an informational recycling guide.
8. Working phones will be advertised through our website and people can buy them at a reduced rate.  After listing the phone for a period of time and no one wants it, the team will donate them to charity.
9. Buyers will receive their cell phone through mail or they can pick it up at our booth if they want to avoid shipping fee.
10. Non working phones will be send to the phone manufacture.
11. Other features will be added as we find necessary or that add value to our project.
